# unAInimo — project context

## What this repo is

**unAInimo** is a PWA that adapts the Unanimo board-game idea to LLMs: several "players" receive the **same stimulus** (a concept from a fixed pool), each produces **exactly eight words** under shared rules, then a **Judge** clusters words semantically so the backend can score **conceptual overlap** (Unanimo-style) and **position / priority alignment** (Synchronicity). See `README.md` for scoring formulas and API surface.

## Primary goal (why it exists)

The motivating **experiment** is to **compare how different models respond to identical inputs** under the same constraints—not open-ended chat, but a **structured, comparable** output (eight words, forbidden roots/numbers/symbols). The game is the **protocol**: it turns "same prompt, different models" into metrics and a UI (HTMX + SSE) instead of ad-hoc side-by-side transcripts.

When changing behavior, preserve: **same stimulus to all players**, **parallel generation**, **shared temperature** (spec: `0.7`), and **judge-mediated semantics** so scores stay comparable across runs.

## Stack (do not casually replace)

- **Backend**: Go, hexagonal layout — `cmd/server`, `internal/domain`, `internal/ports`, `internal/service`, `internal/adapters/{llm,storage,http}`, `web/`.
- **Frontend**: HTML templates + Tailwind + HTMX; **SSE** for live word stream and judge completion.
- **Ops**: Docker Compose; Redis with in-memory fallback.
- **Ollama**: Default API base is **`http://192.168.1.130:11434`** when `OLLAMA_BASE_URL` is unset; long **`OLLAMA_HTTP_TIMEOUT`** (default 900s) and **serial players** (default on for Ollama) avoid GPU-queue client timeouts; embedding-only tags filtered from `/api/tags`.

